      "date": "2025-09-28 18:36:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI attempted to fix the build errors present in this patch and succeeded. Yay! Now, keep in mind I barely have any idea what I am doing, so please doublecheck the changes I made to make sure they make sense.\n\nThis service is only provided in hopes to be useful and reduce latency from push to getting actual results in the face of trivial code errors\n\nHere's summary of my changes:\nThe change in this patch is a **fix to a syntax and structure issue** in the `fld_index.c` file, specifically:\n\n- **Removed an incomplete function declaration** that was incorrectly placed in the middle of the file.\n  - The line `int fld_index_lookup(const struct lu_env *env, struct lu_server_fld *fld,` was left dangling without a proper closing parenthesis or parameter list, causing a compile error.\n- **Restored proper function definition** by moving the function declaration to its correct position (before the function body), ensuring the function is properly declared and defined.\n\n### Summary:\nThis patch fixes a compile error caused by a malformed or misplaced function declaration in `fld_index.c`. It removes the incomplete `int fld_index_lookup(...` declaration that was interrupting the code flow and ensures the function is properly declared and defined, allowing the code to compile correctly.",
